Sure! Below is a simple HTML file for a Tom Hanks fan app. This app includes embedded CSS for styling and JavaScript for interactivity. You can copy and paste the entire code into a `.html` file and open it in a web browser.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Tom Hanks Fan App</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            background-color: #f0f0f0;
            color: #333;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 20px;
        }
        header {
            text-align: center;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
        }
        h1 {
            color: #2c3e50;
        }
        .movie-list {
            list-style-type: none;
            padding: 0;
        }
        .movie-item {
            background: #fff;
            border: 1px solid #ddd;
            border-radius: 5px;
            margin: 10px 0;
            padding: 10px;
            transition: background 0.3s;
        }
        .movie-item:hover {
            background: #e0e0e0;
        }
        button {
            padding: 10px 15px;
            background-color: #3498db;
            color: white;
            border: none;
            border-radius: 5px;
            cursor: pointer;
        }
        button:hover {
            background-color: #2980b9;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

<header>
    <h1>Welcome to the Tom Hanks Fan App!</h1>
    <p>Discover some of the best movies featuring Tom Hanks.</p>
</header>

<section>
    <h2>Favorite Movies</h2>
    <ul class="movie-list" id="movieList">
        <li class="movie-item">Forrest Gump</li>
        <li class="movie-item">Saving Private Ryan</li>
        <li class="movie-item">Cast Away</li>
        <li class="movie-item">The Green Mile</li>
        <li class="movie-item">Big</li>
    </ul>
    <button id="addMovieButton">Add a Movie</button>
</section>

<script>
    document.getElementById('addMovieButton').addEventListener('click', function() {
        const movieName = prompt("Enter the name of the movie:");
        if (movieName) {
            const movieList = document.getElementById('movieList');
            const newMovieItem = document.createElement('li');
            newMovieItem.className = 'movie-item';
            newMovieItem.textContent = movieName;
            movieList.appendChild(newMovieItem);
        }
    });
</script>

</body>
</html>
```

### How to Use:
1. Copy the code above.
2. Open a text editor (like Notepad, VSCode, or any code editor).
3. Paste the code into the editor.
4. Save the file with a `.html` extension (e.g., `tom_hanks_fan_app.html`).
5. Open the saved file in a web browser.

You will see a simple fan app where you can view a list of Tom Hanks movies and add new ones by clicking the "Add a Movie" button. Enjoy!
